In a recent press conference, President Trump expressed his frustration with the ongoing investigation by Special Counsel Robert Mueller. He referred to it as a "witch hunt" and criticized the Attorney General for recusing himself. Trump also mentioned the recent raid on the office of his personal attorney, calling it a disgraceful situation. He emphasized that his focus is on important matters such as Syria and the fight against ISIS. The President also discussed the stock market drop and the need to strengthen the military. He thanked Ambassador John Bolton for joining his team and expressed confidence in his abilities. Trump stated that a decision regarding the response to the chemical weapons attack in Syria would be made soon. He did not provide further details on the responsible party or the potential military options.